Cia. de Saneamento do Parana , a
Brazilian water utility, will invest 211.6 million reais ($105
million) in water and sewage projects in the southern city of
Curitiba through 2017.  Sanepar, as the company is known, will invest 82.3 million
reais of that amount in water works this year, the Curitiba,
Brazil-based utility said last week in a statement. The company
invested 159 million reais in the city the last two years.  To contact the reporter on this story:
